   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>(lines 6-15) There is also reported the unproductive category for the 41st year: land flooded owing to water discharged from the plains at Tebetnu from the outburst of the bend of the river Montilas by Hiera Nesos and the marshes by Kerkeesis and Ptolemais of the Bee-keepers which became overfull and flooded the adjacent royal land, 76 1/2 arouras 397 1/2 1/3 artabas, of which 25 1/2 were in copper, 40 in lentils, 40 in beans, and the individual items are: --of Petesouchos son of Horos, as credited, 3 arouras at 5 1/4 1/24 (artabas to the ar.), 15 1/2 1/3 art.</ab>
         </div>
